  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1856945437" />
    <a title="Sally" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1736231-sally"><img alt="Sally" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1411505393p2/1736231.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1856945437?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sally" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sally" href="/user/show/1736231-sally">Sally</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781572701281" href="/book/show/1689227.The_Danger">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1856945437" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1964739113757242496">Andrew Douglas, a kidnapping specialist, is hired to solve a series of kidnappings connected with horse racing, including that of a female Italian jockey and a little British boy. The novel is exciting, Andrew is logical and tough, yet with a soft side that makes him appealing to Alesia, the jockey. Another great book by Dick Francis. I heard this read by Tony Britton, who is absolutely masterful in creating different character voices who are all quite believable. I look forward to hearing somet</span>
  <span id="freeText1964739113757242496" style="display:none">Andrew Douglas, a kidnapping specialist, is hired to solve a series of kidnappings connected with horse racing, including that of a female Italian jockey and a little British boy. The novel is exciting, Andrew is logical and tough, yet with a soft side that makes him appealing to Alesia, the jockey. Another great book by Dick Francis. I heard this read by Tony Britton, who is absolutely masterful in creating different character voices who are all quite believable. I look forward to hearing something else read by him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1964739113757242496" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
